Description: recursive DNS resolver with DNSSEC validation
 Knot Resolver is a caching full DNS resolver implemented in C, LuaJIT, and Python.
 It consists of a resolver library, a resolving daemon, and a manager.
 Its modular architecture keeps the core small and efficient while providing a
 state-machine-like API for extensions.
 .
 The Lua-based module system, shared cache, and fast FFI bindings enable deep integration
 into the resolution process and flexible deployment of recursive DNS services.
 .
 Unlike threaded resolvers, Knot Resolver uses a shared-nothing architecture with an
 optional shared MVCC cache, enabling horizontal scaling through multiple independent workers.
 .
 Knot Resolver Manager simplifies running multiple resolver workers with zero-downtime
 reconfiguration via declarative YAML/JSON configuration and an optional HTTP API for dynamic changes.

